 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Saleem</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Angrier, you are a fucktard.  ANY 60 Shaman with a brain, and a copy of torpor will kill you. It's that simple.  They'll laugh as you run yourself out of mana chain ToNing or dotting them (while they dispell the dots).  Please find a 60 shaman with a brain, duel him, and come back so we can all laugh at your corpse.</P><P>Some things that *may* get you the kill ONCE against a shaman (ie once they learn you can't do these anymore)</P><P>Harmshield at the beginning of the duel, odds are good malo is their first cast, if they don't notice that it didn't stick you have a huge advantage. (This is kinda a long shot if they know about the DMF stacking bug or they recognize the HS spell effect).</P><P>Do a lot of dispelling to fuck up their buff slots...pray you open up the first one and they don't have any clickies (or forget to use them).  Dispell torpor.</P><P>If you kept malo off yourself, they're gonna start to wonder why the hell their poison dots aren't landing.  Use the confusion to your advantage by inflicting damage as fast as possible.</P><P>Through all of this, try to keep the pet unrooted if possible.</P><P>An easy way to defeat enchanters is to cast disease cloud on yourself.  Nuff said.</P><P>In a cleric duel, you're counting on the pet interrupting.  Wait for the right moment to make the kill.  Be conservative with your mana.</P><P>Bards are annoying.  They can dispell every 3 seconds.  They will charmsploit and poof your pet.  Their melee is weak, but enough to interrupt most higher level/longer casting spells.  Chain Deflux is about the only way to defeat a good bard.</P><P>Wizard duels are all tactics.  You need to fake them out...a lot.  HS/QVoX are essential.  Any smart casting class is going to keep their first buffslot open to dispell dots easily.  A quick dispell can fuck up their buffslots enough to land a dot or two.  Otherwise you want to keep the pet on them for interrupts.</P><P>The second a shadowknight has you down to 1k hp, he wins.  Period.  For most of us that's around 50% hp.  A smart shadowknight will dispell your dots and try to win the mana game with taps.</P><P>A Pally duel is similar to a shaman...they have Celestial Cleansing....step1 = run you oom.  step2 = you die, fast.</P><P>Mages are a joke.  Chain ToN &gt; Mage.</P><P>Against any pure melee, the pet focus is a huge boon.  The focused spectre is around as fast as a jbooted PC, kite them around...if they stop to deal with the pet, inflict damage.  ArchLich, taps, and a focused pet &gt; any pure melee.</P><P>Angrier has one good point in all his retarded babble.  Use heat blood as it costs less mana, and try to get them to waste dispell charges.  Think of creative ways to fake people out.</P><P>Against anyone, a good deal of shit talking and some headgames may be enough to pull out the win.  Discuss a tactic with them, use a completely different one and laugh as they try to counter the tactic you were discussing.</P><P>If you aren't on a PvP server, learn to set a few parameters before the duel.  Any retard can run out of spell casting range and regen up, stretching the duel into a 6 hour ordeal and possibly stalemating it.  Being out of spellcasting range for longer than some set time (10 seconds works) should be insta loss.  Things like manaburn make the duel a waste of time...ban it beforehand and test your true skill.  If you lose to HT from a shadowknight, duel him again right away...make him earn his win this time.</P><P>Anyone who knows the classes well, and has the right equipment can be a potent dueler.  Knowing your own class is not enough.  Learn about your opponent before dueling them if possible.  Anticipate him and find ways to counter his tactics.</P><P>-Saleem<BR>Warlock of Xegony<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=183649" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=183649</a></font></td>
