        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Cerilius</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I have to laugh at this silly flame war.</P><P>Necromancers, while far from being the best PvP class, are still decent PvPers. There are a vast number of fighting techniques available to the caster, and most of the "skilled" people you'll run into on a PvP server have at least one weakness. Maybe they don't understand how to defend themselves against the Siphon Strength/Shadow Vortex deadlock. Maybe they have no instaclick items or SoW potions, and are unaware of how valuable it is to be faster than your opponent. Or perhaps they're clueless when it comes to range kiting -- an art that requires detailed knowledge of the casting times of your and your opponent's offensive spells. A lot of PvP is finding your opponent's weakness and exploiting it. If you want to devise one unbeatable strategy and slaughter everyone with it, knowing comfortably in your mind that the game mechanics don't allow them to stand a chance, then reroll as a ranger, a bard, or a shadowknight.</P><P>That having been said, a perfect necro is still at a loss to another perfect player. As others have mentioned, it takes almost no skill to beat a necro as a hybrid class, especially as one who has his epic/primal and a load of resist gear. With a fungi tunic and a velium brawl stick, a well-played druid can casually emerge victorious in a duel with a necro without breaking a sweat. Now that golem wands/egg pumice have been nerfed, even an enchanter can kill a good necro.</P><P>One thing to bear in mind is that almost every "skilled" player is a bad PvPer by an objective standard. Learn more about PvP mechanics and the different strategies available to you. Don't worry so much about what a "perfect" druid or enchanter would do, and concentrate on hitting your opponent's weaknesses instead. If your opponent is very skilled and has made it clear that you are going to lose, gate. Then, after medding up, look for the next person to kill.</P><P>Cerilius D`Nixx<BR>54 Necromancer, VZ</font></td>
      </tr>
