while spamming your jboots.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>There's no way in hell on any server that a druid is going to kill me, much less with melee.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Of course he won't *kill* you -- you can always gate. But in a formal duel (where the gater loses), all a druid needs to do to win is kill your pet, dispel your dots, melee you, and keep clicking his ES arms. You could go into lich form and deflux him every 60 seconds, running out of range of his dot arms, but if he has a fungi tunic/chloroplast chestplate, you wouldn't be able to keep up with his melee.</P><P>Of course, most druids are idiots -- you could kill a hundred of them before you found one who knew what he was doing.</P><P>Cerilius D`Nixx<BR>54 Necromancer</font></td>
