een up.  I wouldn't hesitate to SS-Gate, HS-Gate, whatever.  Chanters with the initiative are bad news to low HP people like me.</P><P>Isn't that a little more reasonable?  At least for pvp servers.  Initiative is so important, because the attacked party loses a few beats of timing, doesn't have good spells memmed, doesn't have pet up/buffed, doesn't have the right buffs, in the right order...  And all of that is crucial.  And then there's group pvp, probobly more important than any of this and even less simple to analyze.</P><P>Personally, I'd say this in summation - we Necros have real killing power, and Chanters don't - but chanters can definately kill casters, including unlucky Necros who don't escape when they're in trouble.</P><P>Ulyn Vindix, 53rd, SZ<BR>(Yeah yeah, I'm low.  But I talk to the warlocks, and I've seen enough of these silly "paper battles" to recognize the fallacies.)</P><P> </font></td>
