      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Cerilius</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>I can't fucking stand range kiting and all that...it drives me batshit.  It simply is not a valid tactic.  I gave ten seconds as an example, because it is easy to be out of range by accident and that is not what I'm trying to prevent at all.  If you can turn around and run the other way, so can I...if you're going to run to opposite ends of the zone, you may as well not even bother to duel.  Range kiting is gaytactic numero uno...if I see it, I'm gonna cast harmshield and get gate up...and then gate.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>While you're certainly entitled to that opinion, recognize that all this could be said of jousting, too. With a 60-second limit, the fight still gets somewhere, just a little more slowly (as in a jousting match). Range kiting doesn't mean running in a straight line and doing nothing. It's just a smart way to make the recast delay on spells less significant. That being said, running in one direction without stopping and casting is about as lame as one melee zig-zagging and strafing around another, with no intention of landing a single hit.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Er, you make up an Annul in two ticks...faster than you can recast.  It's basically free.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Annul starts out "free". Likewise, the enchanter's Root starts out almost free (he would regen 22 of the 30 mana he used during those two ticks). The thing to bear in mind is that unlike the enchanter, your HP is dropping fast because of Arch Lich. When the time comes to Touch of Night that wandering fire beetle, you will have just lost 405 of your mana to 82 of the enchanter's (adding up the mana he'd lose rooting the pet during that time). Because of this, an unfocused pet is a weak offensive tool against an enchanter who knows what he's doing.</P><P>Of course, you *could* switch to using Nullify (which for the purpose of dispelling pets is just as good) instead of Annul, saving you 20 mana per cast. By doing this, you can reduce your mana spent to around 200, which is better, but it still falls short of the enchanter's 82. (If you're fighting another rooting class, however, so that you can use Vexing, you can force his mana pool to run out much faster than yours -- which, interestingly, isn't possible with Annul Magic.)</P><P>Cerilius D`Nixx<BR>54 Necromancer</P><P>Edited by - Cerilius on 06/08/2002  16:07:07</font></td>
