 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Richmagne</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> A point that many people who agrue a smart enchanter will always beat a smart necro is simply that they assume any DoT the necro casts can be dispelled instantly by the enchater if the enchanter sets up his buffs correctly.<BR>  This simply is not the case. We also have poison and disease dots that cannot be annuled. Of course they would have to land, but it isnt that hard to do if you play it smart.<BR>  To get a Ebolt to land all you have to do is cast something like boil blood, wait for the enchanter (who we will assume is playing *smart* and has 2 insta buffs, two blank spots, a couple junk buffs, then good buffs) to drop his insta buffs and begin to cast the annul. You then immediately begin to cast annul yourself, and if you watched closely enough yours should hit immediately after his, taking his junk buffs. You then repeat the process, recast boil and wait for him to dispell.<BR>  At this point he knows what you're going to do, but really has no choice if he wants to dispell the pyro. (If he doesnt dispell the dot you can proceed to tap him a bit to drop his hps. Normally once thier hitpoints drop below half they become more cooperative about dispelling future dots, heh ) The second time through you should get to his resist buffs. Without resists buffed up you should be able to land a dot he cant dispell in 2-3 trys and finish him off.<BR>  Notice that so far you've cast harmshield once ( cast it as he trys to Tash, I forgot that )cast 2 boil bloods and 2 annuls. He was casting while you were casting the HS and the annuls, so he's really only had time for about 3 main drains while you were casting the 2 BBs- not nearly enough to stop you from hitting him with ebolts a lifetaps to finishh him.<BR>  The nice thing about this approach is it kills smart chanters and dumb ones alike. The smart ones will have their buffs preset up and try to dispell, the dumb ones either wont have thier buffs set up right or wont dispell your dot. Either way you win. <BR>  I expect everyone to go out and own our favorite local chanter today, happy hunting. )</P><P> </font></td>
